track_notes: Car parked in Wasdale at Overbeck Bridge. This is a linear route from Burnthwaite Farm (B&B) straight up Kirk Fell (unrelenting climb) before proceeding to Pillar. We then climbed the Wainwrights of Little Scoat Fell > Steeple > Red Pike (Wasdale) and the fantastic Yewbarrow to finish at Overbeck Bridge. A tough round of 9.6 miles with over 5200 foot ascent and it felt like it...walk done 01/04/11 for more info see wainwrightsontheair.blogspot.co.uk
track_title: Pillar LD-006 - preceded by Kirk Fell LD-014 + 4 more Wainwrights
